caption: This will be my place to pickup great Jamaican food when I fly into Tampa. Mom's lemon cake is fantastic too. I ordered a curry chicken, goat, and two escovich fish dinners. My brother got the bbq ribs. Everything was incredible.
The food was delicious as always

This is one of my favorite ❤ new spots to hit when I fly into TPA... free parking out front and that rustic setting that reminds me so much about the small homestyle restaurants back in Jamaica. Authentic cooking that brings you back 😋
Was the best place for ethnic jamaican edibles for a reasonable $$. Would recommend the cakes home made.
Food honestly was nasty all of it I got curry goat rice & sweet potatoes didn’t enjoy it
Great food ..mac n cheese on point yessssss

ME & MY SISTER WAS VISITING WE GOOGLE ISLAND REST. THE BEST CHOICE EVER. YES THE FOOD WAS SO BEAUTIFUL TO THE EYES BUT MOST OF ALL IT WAS DELICIOUS. YOU COULD TASTE THE ISLAND FLAVORS. THANKS THE HOST HE WAS SO PROFESSIONAL .FRIENDLY. HAD GREAT MANNERISM. NEVER UNDERESTIMATE THE LOOK OF A BUILDING. P.S. THE GENTLEMAN THAT BAKE THE CAKES. YOU HAVE A BLESSED HAND THE HOMEMADE PUND CAKE. SWEETALICIOUS. KEEP IP GREAT WORK MAY YOU CONTINUE TO BE BLESSED

Please eat here.. This restaurant is a must eat. You won't regret it i promise. Just don't take your mom with you when u go cause that strawberry lemonade tastes so good its gone make you wanna slap yo mama Lol 😂. Thanks one stop jerk center. You just gained a new customer.
Food was outstanding true Jamaican Cuisine large portions n delicious a must try

This place is such a slept on STAPLE of West Tampa. When I lived on Spruce, back when West Tampa was still West Tampa, I used to walk up here all the time for a jerk chicken dinner and I was never dissatisfied. Great home cooked island food, pretty much unrivaled in the near area. Stop sleeping on this place and try it before it becomes another victim of gentrification!!!
Y'all! This is some of the best food I've ever had! Highly recommended😩

Take it from this white girl, do yourself a favor and eat at this place. Everything I had (jerk chicken, okra, and plantains) was absolutely amazing and the people behind the counter made me feel more than welcome. Definitely recommend!
I love this place been going to them for over 10 years. The hospitality is also the best.
The food is absolutely delicious!
The food is delicious!!
The food at One Stop is so amazingly delicious 😋... This is definitely going to be the restaurant I will go to every time I am in the Tampa Bay area!
Jerk chicken, rice, Mac and cheese, and corn bread were all fantastic. The large plate was an excellent portion.
Fabulous✌🏾🏆👏🏽
Always perfect and delicious 😋 😍
Best Jamaican food ever!  Family-owned restaurant.
My favorite curry goat here 👌🏽👌🏽 Their food is legit amazing! Well, now I know where to get some good island food.
Best fish I've ever had. Nice folks also!
Ordered from here and received great quality food and large portions. However no masks were worn during my last visit.

Holy Cow, this restaurant is amazing!! By far, my favorite steakhouse in SF. I have yet to try Alexanders and couple in the West Coast though. While tradition reigns supreme at many of the nation's carnivore temples, you need to have good steak once in a while. My brother one weekend wanted to take me here to eat and he said eat very very light lunch, because I'm taking you out to eat tonight. He made reservations at 8pm, we waited in the bar and piano lounge for about 10min, while we enjoyed a cocktail.
My food was delivered expeditiously, fresh and full of flavor. One Stop Jerk Center is one of the best JERK stop's in the Bay.

First time I went to One stop jerk,and man let me tell you you get very great portion size for what your paying for and the food tastes so good that once’s I was done eating my plate, I wanted to go back and buy one more, the oxtail my girlfriend loved them and I enjoyed them to, the ribs where good,Mac was amazing cornbread was amazing my food was so good, I’m coming back for more, and when my friends and family come to visit me I’m taking them to this spot right here to get some real good cooking now.
We drove down from Destin FL I found this restaurant on TripAdvisor. Omg this has been the best food we had and we had been on a 10 day vacation. Omg I wish I had the mac and cheese and oxtail now.

I was in London for a week with my family, and it took us about 4 days in of eating Pret a Manger every single morning before we found this gem!!! This food is filling, a good taste of authentic English breakfast, has super quick service (about a 5-10 minute wait for a home cooked breakfast), and to top it off, the pricing is totally fair! The tea is so much better too, in my American opinion. Please check this place out if you get a chance!
Absolutely delicious,  had the ribs and the portions are well worth your dollars! This is now my new favorite place to eat . Just amazing all the way around. Thank you! Don't ever change.
Oxtails and customer service was spot on. Better than anything in Atlanta. Wow..
So good an it was cooked fresh
Idk what the last reviewer was talking about ...food here is FIRE. Veggie plate alwayssss hit the spot. Great customer service...food cooked fresh and great prices.
🔥🔥🔥 Food flavorful an great portion sizes!

This food was not good at all. I don’t even write reviews, but I’m beyond upset. The Mac and cheese was bland, the chicken was bland, and the rice. This was NOT Jamaican food at all, and I’m highly disappointed. I wanted to support another business, but Golden Krust and Jamaica Jamaica will continue to get my business. I tried to continue to eat the food since I paid for it, but just couldn’t get through it. I really hate to leave a review like this, but hopefully this help the restaurant and cooks. :(
The food was amazing. But noone had their facemask on in the middle of a pandemic.
Service was great and the food was so amazing. Would definitely recommend stopping by

The owner and her daughters were very welcoming from the beginning, and the food was absolutely amazing! I highly recommend the oxtail as well as the jerk chicken, it’s a must try! We will definitely be back soon!
Tried this a few weeks ago. The food is fresh and good, mac cheese was great, fish was seasoned to the bone. Best snapper I ever had.

My husband and I called to order our food. We both got the ox Mack an cheese and greens and corn bread. Let me tell you the meat falls right off the bone. The portions are an amazing size. And it was decent priced I loved it. I think we have the best place for our Jamaican food ❤️
I ❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤ the food, the punches and the service.

Omg! This  restaurant has the best food.  Customer service is outstanding. Bottom line, delicious food, large portions, respectful customer service. Cannot say enough positive things about this heavenly eatery! Must have!!!

The food was delicious. I had the curry goat rice and peas and mac & cheese. Very tasty my compliments to the chefs. They truly know how to prepare a great meal. And they were very friendly and welcoming. Thanks
This place is awesome! Awesome people, awesome food, awesome prices. This is an literal gem and you wouldn't be disappointed by stopping by sometime.
"The 'Go To Spot' Every Week!"
Great food
One of the best spots I've visited. Good is seasoned and good.. no need to season...
Found this place on my way back home from the Airport. Glad I stopped by! Food was excellent and the service was nothing less.
Great food and good lunch specials

If I could give this place a - Stars I would.  The place looks like a Nightmare come true. I still walked in because I drove from BFE to get here and it was SCARIER Inside.  There was 1 Family eating up tons of Food at the Bar. I asked what they had Today and the answer was, "We're currently OUT OF EVERYTHING."  As if that wasn't enough, they then read down each Item on the Menu 1 by 1 to let Me know they were OUT OF EVERYTHING.  #nightmare #wasteoftime
I am a good customer of this restaurant.  After numerous visits, I have never been disappointed.  The food is delicious, the service is excellent and the atmosphere is always friend.
Local Jamaican restaurant mom & pop place, good food
Very friendly and amazing food!!
So tasty.  Well seasoned.
This is my personal go-to for Oxtails and Cabbage for years! Always fast and friendly service.
Love the fish! Everything is delicious!
I came here after seeing “good reviews” but to my surprise they were closed at 6:17pm when their time says open till 7pm. Wow, such an inconvenience.
I never come to Tampa without eating here. It's always freshly cooked food with a welcoming environment.
Fish was A1, I had the red snapper; it was made well cooked with delicacy and love. The owners cook like you're apart of the family an excellent place to stop for a great meal.
This is the best Carribean cuisine restaurant in Tampa Bay.Everything is fresh from scratch.Been eating here for 10 + years.Its family owned.Very humble family.
Awesome food
Like them hole in the wall dives? This a good pick!

Visiting Tampa and wanted some good Jamaican food. Called another spot after seeing reviews but no one picked up. So I tried calling here. Person who answered was very kind. Food was prepared quickly.  Lady was kind as well in person which I definitely appreciated . Two teenagers in kitchen as well. Food looked good. But once I actually tasted it when I got back to my hotel, it was quite bad. I ordered 3 meals...oxtail for me and jerk chicken and brown stew for my kids.The meats were passable but the rice was parboiled rice that was overcooked with a sprinkle of red kidney  beans...was soppy and way too salty!  Definitely not Jamaican rice and peas. We got sides of macaroni and cheese because there was no more plantains and though I knew mac and cheese is not Jamaican cuisine , I was hungry. It tasted like it came from the box. Obviously I could've cooked my own oxtail and rice and peas as I'm Jamaican and can actually cook, but since I was visiting from out of town, I had to eat out but I was left very disappointed, out $30+( also bought soft drinks), and me and fam were still hungry as we couldn't continue eating this. I would give a 5 for customer service but a 1 for the food.
Best Jamaican in Hillsborough County! The Red Snapper is everything
Rice not cook. Cabbage spoil and the Oxtail was not coming off the bone. I honestly had to throw the food away.
Food was cold and the curry was raw. Would Never return threw away all of the food.
Family owned and operated and makes some of the best food in Tampa for a great price. This hidden jewel is definitely a top 5 spot for me in Tampa!

All i can say is WOW! I come here once, sometimes TWICE a week and the food is always AMAZING! Staff is soooo sweet i know them personally. Your not going to find better jerk chicken than this in tampa. I moved from Tampa and i STILL make the drive to get my jerk chicken fix!!! I have a plate sitting on my lap right now! and idek how i was able to write this long review b4 eating it, so , GOODBYE!
Lorna will make you feel right at home with your Jamaican Soul Food Experience!

Stopped here before we got on the plane to go back home and The food was delicious to say the least! The dive style restuarant has a homey feel. Good for eating in or carry out. The icing on the cake was the owner who everyone calls Grandma! She was super friendly and welcoming. AND also happen to be a fellow alumni of the Thorobred Nation, Kentucky State University. What are the odds? My parents live near by so they will get to visit her and we plan to send our love every chance we get! Please give this place a try! The oxtails and goat were amazing! As were the side dishes except I did t get to try the yams because they were sold out so someone go try them and comment to fill me in. Happy eating #kingcritic #localguide
Everything was delicious,  rice was tender, cabbage was flavorful, jerk chicken was scrumptious.
Food and prices are absolutely amazing! Visiting from St. Louis, MO. We tried 2 other places before them and they were the best!! Also amazing customer service!
Great island food. Go try it. Get the oxtails you'll love it
Best in town
The rice was old and my curry goat was bland and tough. The lunch special was too small. The only reason I give 3 instead of 1 is ive had better once before.
If you are from Jamaica don't order from these people. Their foods have nothing in common with authentic Jamaican food. Curry goat tastes awful,  it's indescribable. Never never again!
Amazing as always! I would have really enjoyed more of the owners homemade hot sauce, but they ran out. Perhaps they could make a larger portion since it is so popular? Otherwise, great experience
Food is always fresh and they pack the 5$ lunch which is great to find a meal so good and home cooked for 5$ a hidden gem of West Tampa!
Love the food!!!! Best around, cant beat the prices!!
BEST JAMAICAN FOOD IVE EVER HAD IN MY LIFE OMG!!!!!!!!!
Love it

Delicious. The picture below is the curry chicken plate. Again, delicious. Don't be fooled by the outside look. Is literally a place that I wouldn't have gone if I just saw it. I came across by referral. And I truly appreciate it. Great food, great people and great prices. Thank you.
Very slow and they missed the fries
Awesome food and great prices.

This is where you should go if you want the best in Ja - merican dishes. From the moment you walk inside you are greeted with the friendlies of costumer service personnel you will ever find in a restaurant. I love their oxtail and the way it melts off the bone in my mouth. But what keeps me coming back each day is the combination of the Jamaican and American food combine which makes this "island restaurant" stands out from this rest. I which this family owned restaurant nothing but prosperity and keep feeding the city of Tampa, surrounding communities and last but not least in coming visitors like me........
I love the food and the people every time I go. Simply delicious, I can’t find better Jamaican food anywhere. And just wonderful people.
Not real thrilled with this one.
Great Food!! Esp. the Snapper!

Diamond! Excellent family owned business. Food was prepared nicely and service was fast as I was on a lunch break. The owner and I chatted for a bit.  She had been there 16years. Authenticity Approved! I will be coming back for sure!
Amazing food! Wonderful ladies as well 😁

This was my first time hearing about this place and I decided to order it from uber eats. I got a large meal and they gave a lot more food than I thought they would. It's by far the absolute best Caribbean place I've ever eaten from. Everything is seasoned perfectly and tastes so good
Fast service.  Food not to bad.  Will try again.
Whole snapper and 2 sides
Very good.
Sweet and friendly atmosphere. The food is as divine as it is scrumptious. Truly authentic in  hospitality and service. One of my spots to go to when I treat myself to quality eating.
Awesome food

Friendly people just like home owners a very sweet person always happy and friendly

Food is great
My favorite Jamaican restaurant since i was in high school.

This is what we mean by home cooked! The food is great!!! And the owner is lovely!!! Try the corn bread and mac and cheese!!!! And everything else!!!
This is not Jamaican rice and peas. The food was horrible, the goat meat was undercooked and the so called rice and peas only had one single peas on it. Would never return, wasted my money.
The women person working was so friendly and treated me very well. I was handed great food.  The prices are good to. I will be back!!!
It was ok but not authentic Jamaican cuisine.  I won't be going back....
it's a small place but the food is really good
Good Food 👍
Authentic Food & Host
Second time here and the jerk chicken is on point again. Great west Indian spot.

My food was delish! Second time coming here and I happened to meet the owner this time. She was very kind and took good care of me. I wish they closed at a later time, but overall food was very good. I will advise, this restaurant is a bit American, so there are soul food options in addition to the Caribbean cuisines.
Well done. Can't complain at all
I love it. Coming back

Not Jamaican food! The jerk was covered in a barbeque sauce. The rice and peas were made with yellow seasoned rice. I told them i wanted rice a peas. That us not what i got. It's dark and dingy. Not going back.
Another Tampa secret...

I went by based on reviews but I wasn't 100% satisfied. The curry goat and cabbage were delicious! The rice wasn't horrible but definitely bland and Mac was not homemade. Minor stuff so I would try it again.
The food is very delicious and the owner and her family are very home welcoming. I love their Curry Chicken platter and the mac & cheese
My boyfriend and I come 3-4 times a month and love it!  I love seeing a family business ran so well.  Every item on the menu is amazing!!
I just moved in down the way and went here for my first time. The food was great!!
Just ate lunch here. I've eaten at at least 20 Jamaican restaurants and this one by far is the best. Laid back and relaxed. HIGHLY recommended. Live in Lakeland and this is my lunch spot in Tampa
Good food.  Nice people

This place is the best place to come for Jamaican food. The staff is very friendly and courteous. Will definitely be back when ever we are in this area again. The pineapple tea is also delicious. Excellent food for the prices and amount of food you get.
Too Damn Good...
The food was delicious and the staff was friendly and helpful
The food was really good,and the service was great.
The place is very clean and the people are courtesy, and the food is more than delightful. They give you a large portion if whatever you order. More food for your money. I loved the place!
It was quiet, staff polite and the food was great.
The oxtails are delicious and the plates are huge so I feel like I got my money's worth. I would definitely recommend this restaurant to my family and friends.

I was working in the area so I 'Googled' restaurants near me.. so glad I did. I was around 1/2 mile from this place. I ordered the jerk chicken,  comes with yellow rice and 2 sides..I chose the corn bread and the yams. It was so much I thought I'd have leftovers for dinner...nah, it was so good I ate the whole thing. The added hot sauce, a concoction of scotch bonnet and jalapeño peppers gave it that perfect heat! Loved it. Will definitely be back when in the area.
Authentic jamaican food served with a smile. The escovitch red snapper is mouth watering.
The agree with the other reviews, the jerk chicken and cornbread are very good!! I'm still thinking about the cornbread....
Some of the best food in West Tampa
Best Jamaican food in Tampa Bay, the corn bread is to die for and the entire menu is delicious.

The lady who owns it opened early and even though everything wasn't finished cooking the things that were are great. I got the jerk chicken and rice and asked for it to be spicy so she added some of her own sauce and it was awesome
No fried plantain. Sucks for them. Walked right out.

It's doesn't have curb appeal but don't let that stop you from coming in here. It's setup like a small diner. The lady who runs it is all Jamaican and cooks some amazing food. I've had the goat, ox tail, curry chicken. The corn bread is great and the other sides are very tasty. A box of lunch will set you back around $5. :)
